28:48.000 --> 28:51.000
And in fact, certain contradictions began emerging

28:51.000 --> 28:54.000
in the foundations of the calculus.

28:54.000 --> 28:58.000
So people thought it was very important to try and construct it on a rigorous foundation.

28:58.000 --> 29:03.000
And Koshy, Dedekin, and a variety of other people throughout the 19th century did that.

29:03.000 --> 29:06.000
The great achievement, in a way, of 19th century mathematics

29:06.000 --> 29:08.000
was the rigorization of mathematics

29:08.000 --> 29:12.000
and setting it on a firm foundation developing theories of limits

29:12.000 --> 29:16.000
of infinite sequences of convergence and so on.

29:16.000 --> 29:19.000
And so all of that was a great achievement.

29:19.000 --> 29:21.000
And Frager was basically saying,

29:21.000 --> 29:23.000
